This Jummah I’ve started using @mysalahmat to relearn my prayers and I also started introducing Miran to his children’s prayer mat. These mats have been such a blessing for us in our home and have allowed me to feel connected to God again. My spiritual journey is always in need of improving and I’m thankful such a tool has been invented to allow that for me and so many others. 
🔸The adult version is great for reconverts or those relearning to pray again. 
🔸The children’s version is great for children learning to pray and learning the correct placement. 
🔸We’re excited for this journey as we continue to use them! 🙏🏼

Not to mention these make great gifts for your loved ones! 

#prayer #mysalahmat #family #jummahmubarak #islam #god

Birthday Hair 🤎
My lady is going on maternity leave so we decided on something easy to manage, low maintenance and a hint of red undertones🫶🏼
I absolutely love how she surprises me every-time! It’s a nice feeling to get in the chair and be able to say “I trust you” to do whatever you want! 

For my cut and style we went with the usual layers along with chopping off the dead ends just to make my hair healthy and alive again 👩🏻

My hair journey has come a long way especially with postpartum hair loss and I’m forever thankful for it!

We did it! 🙌🏼 We made it to the end of 2️⃣0️⃣2️⃣2️⃣ through the best and worst life had to offer! 
I’m a completely different person now than I was in the beginning of the year. Life challenges and gifts really helped me grow. From going through the trenches of pregnancy, (re)learning each other in marriage and fighting hard to make it work, being blessed with the best gift any parent could ask for, to even living out of suitcases at an apartment to finally moving into our very first home 🏡 🔑 I couldn’t be more grateful and appreciative of the love and tears that were poured into shaping us for the better. All praise to God for finally giving us a golden season of harvest after so much sabr (patience)🙏🏼

I do have to give a special thank you to my family who flew in from different states to help me physically, mentally, and emotionally during my new motherhood experience, unpacking into our new home, and helping with baby Miran so he experienced all the warmth and love when I was just trying to keep myself from drowning some days. Especially my mom and sister who would be a phone call away and on the next flight when I couldn’t hold it together some days. For showing up and even hearing me in my silent moments as I navigated a whole new life of balancing marriage, motherhood, and staying true to myself. The reassurance that love is given no matter the distance has allowed me the strength to keep going even on my worst days! 

#2022  #endoftheyear #newyear #2023 #family #love

Welcoming Ramadan into our home 🌙🙏🏼
I’m so excited to carry on a tradition of decorating our home and taking part in memorable experiences for my little family for many Ramadans to come. 

I saw a post today that resonated with me as a Muslim mom. That if we don’t practice our religion to where our children learn from us and see love for Islam we will be eventually left with descendants who will forget about Allah. That is such a scary thought for me. That the love for this dunya and focus on the wrong things can eventually lead to a decline of our religion. We see it happening so much in todays world and I hope we understand the power we have to allow our children to love Islam through gentle understanding and actions instead of them running away from it. 
I hope all that are celebrating have a blessed Ramadan ❤️

#ramadan

This Ramadan I will be supporting MusCare. MusCare is a grassroots nonprofit organization assisting families in the U.S. and providing humanitarian relief worldwide. Whether it’s building homes in Nigeria or providing access to safe drinking water in Pakistan, let’s join efforts to help continue making a difference.

To help me reach my fundraising goal of $2500 simply donate on the link in my bio. You can even set up a recurring donation of just $1 a month on their website at www.muscare.org/donate.

https://www.gofundme.com/f/hamdas-ramadan-appeal-for-muscare

Together we can make a change.

  #muscare #ramadan #ramadancharity

They say if a friendship lasts past 7 years it lasts a lifetime! Crazy to think we’ve made it this far. From crazy college girls, to finding ourselves through self love, to marriage, and now to motherhood together. Life always has a way of figuring itself out and Im thankful for the genuine souls I get to experience it all with. 
The ones who give without expecting anything in return, where your love and effort is more than enough. The ones who are a phone call away and always know what you don’t say. 

This moment was a full circle moment for me and I pray we all find genuine souls who love us authentically and want to see us do better in this life for the hereafter. The ones who care about your well being and seeing you strive to be better. 

Tag your best friend or person to show your appreciation
Be a little more you and a lot less them🌻

The sadness you get when you realize Ramadan is over is hard to explain. Putting the decorations away until next time. I kept the decor simple this year but I will definitely be adding more items to our collection each Ramadan! 
I’m working really hard on making traditions, and creating an environment for Miran that allows him to love الله (swt) and stay close to Islam. As a new mom it’s been challenging to make that joy for the home yourself but each year I plan to do more to allow that happiness to settle in and stay year round iA.

How has Ramadan ending made you feel?

Finding my mom style has been such a journey! I remember during pregnancy nothing fit and during postpartum depression I threw out all my old clothes thinking I would never wear them again. It’s crazy how you go through such a struggle as the new woman you’ve become while navigating motherhood and everyone seems to overlook you. Taking time to look and feel like yourself becomes the last priority but with time it does get better! Thankful to be feeling like my old self but a better version 🤞🏽

Let’s be honest as we age and go through life our teeth really deteriorate and for me that happened with pregnancy. Who knew pregnancy can mess up your teeth 😳 🦷 
I’ve been working with him to get my dream smile back and here are a few things we are doing:

*Invisalign for bottom teeth
*top front veneers - especially to help with teeth sensitivity 
*regular dental checkups 
*dental health education 

@drjohnkellydds does the above and much more so if you’re in the Chicagoland area check him out and say I sent you
